      "term": "quasiorder",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "C2",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "In mathematics, a relation on a set that is reflexive and transitive, but not necessarily antisymmetric, so different elements can still be related in both directions.",
          "examples": [
            "Every partial order can be seen as a special kind of quasiorder.",
            "The researcher defined a quasiorder to compare the complexity of different algorithms."
          ],
          "collocations": [
